John Carver could stay in charge of Newcastle United until at least the end of the season should he impress over the coming two matches.

The caretaker boss would love the chance to prove his worth at the helm of his hometown club and will communicate as much to owner Mike Ashley, with whom he has a good relationship.

Carver fits the bill of 'head coach' which the club are looking to appoint and he is popular within the dressing room.

