The caretaker boss - pictured here with Steve Stone - has been involved with the club since the early Nineties

His future could well be determined by the outcome of matches against Burnley on New Year’s Day and the FA Cup tie at Leicester City 48 hours later.

But with Newcastle in the relative comfort of mid-table, there is a feeling that Ashley could take a chance on someone like Carver until the end of the campaign, especially if efforts to bring in an external candidate prove troublesome.

The 49-year-old has served on and off at the club in a coaching capacity since the early Nineties having been a reserve-team player with the Magpies before injury curtailed his career.

